description:
Most Christians attend church on Sunday (“the first day of the week”), yet their own Bibles teach that Saturday (“the seventh day”) is the true day of worship. See Exodus 20:8-11; Isaiah 58:13,14. Surprisingly, Jesus Christ kept the seventh-day Sabbath (Luke 4:16), said He was “Lord even of the Sabbath day” (Matthew 12:8), and His own followers still kept that Sabbath after He died on the cross (see Luke 23:56). Not only that, but Jesus never mentioned “the first day of the week” (Sunday) even one time. We appeal to all open-minded searchers for truth to watch this short video to discover the facts, not fiction.   

For everything you need to know about this controversial topic, order Steve Wohlberg’s easy-to-read book, The Truth about the Sabbath.
